definitions: Past tense of rise: move from a lower position to a higher one; come up.
Past tense of rise: increase in number, amount, or intensity.
Past tense of rise: get up from sleeping or resting.
Past tense of rise: (of a sound) become louder or higher in pitch.
examples: The sun rose in the east.
She rose early to catch the train.
A cheer rose from the crowd.
